All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Ant
The class represent an Ant for use by the @code{AntColonyOptimisationSolver} class.
AntColonyOptimisationSolver
Class uses the Ant colony optimisation algorithm to solve an optimised route through a StaticGraph object.
AtomicDouble
Class used to allow Ant threads to manipulate doubles in the pheromone and probabilty matrices without concurrency issues.
BruteForceSolver
Class contains logic to solve TSPGraphs containing node sets using the brute force method by finding the permutations of node orders and traversing them all to find the shortest route.
ChristofidesSolver
Used to find a route through a @code{StaticGraph} using Christofide's algorithm.
Coordinate
Used to represent coordinates.
CoordinateListException
Thrown when the coordinate file reader has viewed all coordinate lists in the file.
CoordinateListFileReader
Class contains the functionality to load graphs from file.
CoordinateListFileWriter
Class contains functionality to handle writing graphs into file by constructing lists of coordinate objects.
CoordinateMover
CoordinateMover class is used to move a coordinate along/up/down one value depending on the method called.
DynamicAntColonyOptimisationSolver
A dynamic travelling salesman problem solver that uses the Ant colony optimization heuristic.
DynamicGraph
Class combines the @code{StaticGraph} and @code{CoordinateMover} classes to create a dynamic travelling salesperson problem graph where the nodes move.
DynamicHilbertFractalCurveSolver
 
DynamicNearestNeighbourSolver
Class uses the nearest neighbour (or greedy) algorithm repeatedly at a set interval to give a route through the moving nodes of a dynamic dgraph.
DynamicSolution
DynamicSolution objects can be used to represent the output of a DynamicSolver objects solutions.
DynamicSolver
 
DynamicTestResult
Holds information output by a test of a dynamic solver.
DynamicTestSuite
 
DynamicTestSuiteResult
Interface for data output by dynamic test suite.
DynamicTestSuiteResultWriter
 
Edge
Used to link two TSPNodes together.
EdgeContainer
Used to manage a set of Edge objects for use in StaticGraph objects.
EdgeStateManager
Used to manage the state of possible edges on a Graph object.
EdgeSuperimpositionException
Exception used to throw an error when two edges attempt to join the same nodes.
EdgeToSelfException
Exception thrown when an attempt is made to create an edge to and from the same node.
Fail
StaticSolver classes will output these objects from their runSolution methods to indicate that the solver failed to find a solution.
FractalDensityException
Thrown when a fractal solver was unable to create a dense enough fractal to visit all nodes on a graph.
Graph
An interface such that we can handle @code{StaticGraphs} and @code{DynamicGraphs} simultaneously.
GraphAnimator
Class runs at frame rate and views the graph object input during construction and then updates the canvas object input during construction to represent what the graph looks like in that during that moment.
GraphGenerator
Class contains functionality to generate StaticGraph objects of certain types or with certain properties.
GraphReader
Reads graphs written by the GraphWriter class.
GraphWriter
Writes graphs in storage format into text files at the path FILE_PATH.
HilbertCurveUnconstructedException
Used to show that an attempt has been made to use a hilbert fractal solver to solve a graph but a curve has not yet been constructed.
HilbertFractalCurveAnimator
Animates a Hilbert fractal curve generated inside a @code{HilbertFractalCurveSolver} onto a java fx canvas.
HilbertFractalCurveSolver
Class constructs a pseudo hilbert fractal curve and then overlays the curve onto a TSP to find an order of traversal.
InvalidGraphException
Exception used to help identify when a solution is fed an invalid graph.
LinKernighanSolver
 
Main
Class used to run and display different solvers at work.
Main2
 
NearestNeighbourSolver
This class takes a graph object as a parameter, and will create a TSP route using the 'Nearest Neighbour Algorithm'.
NoClosestNodeException
Thrown when no closest node can be found to a node.
Node
Used to represent nodes (cities) in the TSP.
NodeContainer
Used to manage sets of nodes for use in StaticGraph objects.
NodeMissedException
Thrown when a HilbertFractalCurveSolver has constructed a curve that has missed a node during a solve.
NodeSuperimpositionException
Exception used to throw an error when two nodes attempt to occupy the same coordinate.
NonExistentNodeException
Exception used to help identify when a solution has encountered a node ID that is not in an initialized Node object.
NoNodeContainerException
Thrown when an attempt is made to modify or interact with a graph that has no node container.
NonSquareCanvasException
Thrown when a canvas input into a @code{HilbertFractalCurveAnimator} or @code{HilbertFractalCurveSolve} is not a perfect square.
PermutationExhaustionException
Exception used to help identify when a @code{Permuter} object viewed all the permutations.
PermutationFocusException
Thrown by a @code{Permuter} object if its @code{focusIdx} attribute encounters list index errors.
Permuter<T>
This class is used to calculate and manage the permutations of a list object.
RadiusExceedingBoundaryException
Used to show when the input radius of an irregular polygon graph is higher than the possible width or height for that irregular polygon.
RepeatedFunctions
Class contains some useful functions that are repeated multiple times in the project (or have no obvious space).
Solution
Used to represent solution outputs in a convenient way.
SolverOutput
 
StaticGraph
Class used to represent and collate data on a travelling salesperson problem graph.
StaticSolver
Interface is used to ensure that StaticSolver implementations can all successfully interact with the StaticTestSuite.
StaticTestSuite
Class used to test Static travelling salesman solutions against a set of pre-constructed graph problems.
Stopwatch
Class can be used to measure execution time of other code by calling start and stop methods, similar to how a stop watch works in real life.
SuperimpositionException
Exception thrown when an object is superimposed on another within the TSP space.
TestResult
 
TestResultFileWriter
 
TestSuiteResult
Class used to hold information about a test suite's execution.
Timer
Timer class used to indicate when a given time period has elapsed using an independant thread.
Vector
